                    "question_type": 1,
                    "question": "一实习生用同一台机器接连独立地制造 3 个同种零件，第 $i$ 个零件是不合格的概率 $p_i=\\frac{1}{i+1}(i=1,2,3)$ ，以 $X$ 表示 3 个零件中合格品的个数, 则 $P\\{X=2\\}=()$.",
                    "analysis": "设 $A_i(i=1,2,3)$ 分别表示第 $i$ 个产品合格, 则\n$$\nP\\left\\{\\overline{A_1}\\right\\}=\\frac{1}{2}, P\\left\\{\\overline{A_2}\\right\\}=\\frac{1}{3}, P\\left\\{\\overline{A_3}\\right\\}=\\frac{1}{4}\n$$\n\n又 3 个零件的独立制造的，所以 $X$ 的分布律为\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& P\\{X=0\\}=P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1 \\bar{A}_2 \\bar{A}_3\\right\\}=P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\overline{A_3}\\right\\}=\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{1}{3} \\frac{1}{4}=\\frac{1}{24} \\text {, } \\\\\n& P\\{X=1\\}=P\\left\\{\\left(A_1 \\bar{A}_2 \\bar{A}_3\\right) \\cup\\left(\\bar{A}_1 A_2 \\bar{A}_3\\right) \\cup\\left(\\bar{A}_1 \\bar{A}_2 A_3\\right)\\right\\} \\\\\n& =P\\left\\{A_1 \\bar{A}_2 \\bar{A}_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1 A_2 \\bar{A}_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1 \\bar{A}_2 A_3\\right\\} \\\\\n& =P\\left\\{A_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_3\\right\\}=\\frac{6}{24}, \\\\\n& P\\{X=2\\}=P\\left\\{\\left(\\bar{A}_1 A_2 A_3\\right) \\cup\\left(A_1 \\bar{A}_2 A_3\\right) \\cup\\left(A_1 A_2 \\overline{A_3}\\right)\\right\\} \\\\\n& =P\\left\\{\\left(\\bar{A}_1 A_2 A_3\\right)\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\left(A_1 \\bar{A}_2 A_3\\right)\\right\\}+P\\left\\{\\left(A_1 A_2 \\overline{A_3}\\right)\\right\\} \\\\\n& =P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{A_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\bar{A}_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_3\\right\\}+P\\left\\{A_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{\\overline{A_3}\\right\\}=\\frac{11}{24}, \\\\\n& P\\{X=3\\}=P\\left\\{A_1 A_2 A_3\\right\\}=P\\left\\{A_1\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_2\\right\\} P\\left\\{A_3\\right\\}=\\frac{6}{24} .\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
